25|$|The 10th Armored Brigade {{from the}} Medina Division and the 22nd Armored Brigade from the Nebuchadnezzar Division, {{supported}} by artillery, launched night {{attacks against the}} U.S. bridgehead at Musayib. The attack was repulsed using tank fire and massed artillery rockets, destroying or disabling every Iraqi tank in the assault. The next morning, Coalition aircraft and helicopters fired on <b>the</b> <b>Republican</b> <b>Guard</b> units, destroying many more vehicles as well as communications infrastructure. <b>The</b> <b>Republican</b> <b>Guard</b> units broke under the massive firepower and the U.S. forces poured through the gap and onward to Baghdad.|$|E
