25|$|During {{the events}} of the Carnation Revolution the convent was encircled by {{military}} rebels, who opposed the Estado Novo regime. The regime's last President, Marcelo Caetano, and forces loyal to his regime were holed-up in the garrison, and eventually surrendered to the future democratic President António de Spínola. The old convent was eventually transformed into the headquarters of <b>the</b> <b>Republican</b> <b>Guard</b> (Guarda Republicana).|$|E
